  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Uterine rupture (UR) is a serious, life-threatening obstetric complication. UR is associated
      with an increased risk of maternal and perinatal morbidity and mortality, particularly in
      developing countries compared to developed countries. UR occurs mainly as a consequence of
      poorly managed labour
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
